{"title":"Enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal-2024-1","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Gastroenterología/Enfermedad inflamatoria intestinal-2024-1.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Enfermedad inflamatoria\\Nintestinal","guid":"rUJn1YlIPBcOT0KkHKaTsQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Definición\\Ny Tipos","guid":"sjlh0TPZcLnTvB4TXBPeGQ","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"EII = CU + EC.","guid":"IdQ1WnR7BnI3VSkMxjAV5w","children":[{"id":"3","parent":"2","text":"• CU: afecta colon.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"2","text":"• EC: afecta cualquier parte del tracto GI.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"• Patología y clínica distintas pero con superposición significativa.","guid":"xaH5sHnLSiUIdwXZc08-pA","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"• Patogénesis pobremente entendida","guid":"PztkSY2yBI2MPSl4A6RgKQ","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"CU:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"• Condición inflamatoria crónica, episodios de inflamación limitada a capa mucosa del colon.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"• Involucra casi siempre el recto, puede extenderse proximalmente de manera continua.","guid":"xRWYfTJpn5SONDXDqWuyFA","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"7","text":"• Términos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"• Proctitis ulcerosa: limitado al recto.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"• Proctosigmoiditis ulcerosa: limitado al recto y colon sigmoide.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"10","text":"• Colitis izquierda: se extiende desde el recto hasta flexura esplénica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"10","text":"• Colitis extensa: se extiende proximalmente a flexura esplénica.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"15","parent":"7","text":"• Clasificación de severidad: leve, moderada o severa.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"1","text":"EC:","guid":"1vb9PyaPBGKq1WlZ4ybikQ","children":[{"id":"17","parent":"16","text":"• Inflamación transmural, áreas de afectación discontinua.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"16","text":"• Involucra comúnmente íleon y colon proximal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"16","text":"• Puede llevar a fibrosis, estenosis, obstrucción, tractos sinusales, microperforaciones y formación de fístulas.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"0","text":"FACTORES DE\\NRIESGO CLÍNICOS","guid":"pTKTIWd1b6sLDBN3RmR9fw","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"Factores de\\Nestilo de vida:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"• Fumar:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"• EC: aumento del riesgo y complicaciones.","guid":"smw-x4qzqu8LHN_QyBTKhg","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"• CU: fumar puede disminuir riesgo y síntomas, cese de fumar aumenta actividad de la enfermedad.","guid":"F0K8TnK_p0sJS-snnBq2rQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"21","text":"• Actividad\\Nfísica:","guid":"h4js1MQVvV0gyR8BFbuLaQ","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"• EC: disminución del riesgo.","guid":"6vX8-pRpbNOD1msnreMoPA","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"• CU: sin asociación clara.","guid":"jZ62PcsFLIMPG_DjqbTVDQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"28","parent":"20","text":"Factores\\Ndietéticos:","guid":"kPw9q2qM1C3GLj5Q1hUujg","children":[{"id":"29","parent":"28","text":"• Fibra: alta ingesta asociada con menor riesgo de EC.","guid":"FU_62o5ZmHgba_xzPlMDMw","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"28","text":"• Grasas: mayor ingesta de grasas correlacionada con mayor incidencia de EII.","guid":"eAjx0OYe6HGOk1t5DBx8vQ","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"28","text":"• Vitamina D: ingesta inversamente asociada con riesgo de EC.","guid":"JgT4oGm7dX8JSKb7Cnzezg","children":[]}]},{"id":"32","parent":"20","text":"Medicamentos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"• Antibióticos: asociados con aumento del riesgo de EC.","guid":"V4x_6uRGetgis4OkT2wjEg","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"• AINEs: pueden aumentar el riesgo de EII.","guid":"pipnFd4tpHLw3nwS7KakQQ","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"• Anticonceptivos orales y terapia de reemplazo hormonal: posible aumento del riesgo de EII.","guid":"8GDV9Q6Bb6StnD9Oo4ll_w","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"32","text":"• Isotretinoína: asociación sugerida con EII, resultados de estudios variables.","guid":"5jW6uqjcsEM9DGZ0d5yQkA","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"20","text":"Otros factores:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"• Apendicectomía:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"39","parent":"38","text":"• EC: posible aumento del riesgo.","guid":"JBDpzc4MHNMLCmnL2m9YVQ","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"38","text":"• CU: posible reducción del riesgo.","guid":"c0h-0kItzikNy6TzPQjdXw","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"37","text":"• Factores psicológicos: estrés puede exacerbar síntomas.","guid":"C_1dHidZE0kkAGDz4h8Frw","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"37","text":"• Obesidad: impacto incierto en desarrollo de EII, puede afectar curso clínico en pacientes con EII establecida.","guid":"pIPIIMRIZ0MdoTdNrx8Nqg","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"37","text":"Exposiciones tempranas:","guid":"O2Tme93od88okDHzNAs-xQ","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"• Lactancia materna y exposición temprana a antibióticos discutidos por separado.","guid":"9L1r-z-IT_6FM8C8Gpe7yQ","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"45","parent":"0","text":"EPIDEMIOLOGÍA","guid":"dwkOOwbM-kLDSCfHzAnxdQ","children":[{"id":"46","parent":"45","text":"• Prevalencia global en aumento, variaciones por región geográfica.","guid":"gLFWCInEglZ2lvA-bpWvDQ","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"45","text":"• Mayor prevalencia en América del Norte, menor en Caribe.","guid":"Tl04_N8_5jHofiSbVFJpOA","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"45","text":"• Incremento en incidencia en países recientemente industrializados de África, Asia y Sudamérica.","guid":"6X8tN4llw7Dz58EA8B3f6A","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"45","text":"• Gradiente norte-sur en incidencia.","guid":"JB1xYR2v-cG2D0iRKL6wGA","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"45","text":"• Factores\\Ndemográficos:","guid":"o0NFmheMbyYUkrrFHv_tfg","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"• Edad: inicio entre 15-30 años, posible segundo pico entre 50-80 años.","guid":"mJHR3h3V4NvIYdL6BrdhIg","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"50","text":"• Sexo: predominancia femenina en EC, masculina en CU.","guid":"J0JE-FW3rC0bM3_h8kDI6A","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"50","text":"• Raza y etnicidad: mayor incidencia en judíos, menor en hispanos y afrodescendientes.","guid":"bGFiwHbdRxTgvJYohDM_1g","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"54","parent":"0","text":"Respuesta\\NInmunitaria en EII","guid":"8hUC1iIXAdz633F_pkfDyw","children":[{"id":"55","parent":"54","text":"• Inmunidad e EII:","guid":"QMjIuwuygIiQcA2Z7IQeew","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"• Respuesta inmune inapropiada frente a microbios intestinales.","guid":"RYah9aoaGbP9ned8Yztpzg","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"55","text":"• Factores del huésped y microbianos involucrados.","guid":"MGL-mE4H06Lys75xrUJo5A","children":[]}]},{"id":"58","parent":"54","text":"• Factores\\NInmunológicos:","guid":"mEX6-E940Hmq_QDw3ySM6g","children":[{"id":"59","parent":"58","text":"• Innatos: Macrófagos, células dendríticas.","guid":"FKwheEN8_4JObE_nAqs-KQ","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"58","text":"• Adaptativos: Células T, citocinas (TNF-α, IL-23).","guid":"s1SghvdCzWcSbs0-eNNmKw","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"54","text":"• Microbiota\\NIntestinal:","guid":"FZuThKSiPzm5Llx6bf46qw","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"• Disbiosis → Activación inmune anormal.","guid":"XIM8HLJhfqEXLRcWz5D73A","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"• Bacterias comensales vs. patógenas.","guid":"QBYu087hbnsfDV7Q5fOEsQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"54","text":"• Factores\\NGenéticos:","guid":"JswyY0ZEoC_rvHYT-ekodw","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"• Polimorfismos (NOD2, IL23R).","guid":"lOgkR77n0LKljgEA09AaMA","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"64","text":"• Susceptibilidad hereditaria.","guid":"HweX5qVmP3-gLYztrGf3ig","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"0","text":"Manifestaciones\\NClínicas y Diagnóstico","guid":"m-tYEHFHXcr4_1QxfNouzQ","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"• Crohn\\N(EC):","guid":"LlFTIaT5sY4tMhZlfWnKNA","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"• Síntomas: Dolor abdominal, diarrea, pérdida de peso, fatiga.","guid":"6x5yMeBqNm9XWhx2wRi7uw","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"• Signos: Inflamación transmural, fístulas, estenosis.","guid":"6AHCr5M5vA5VoFCByzgcpQ","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"68","text":"• Diagnóstico: Colonoscopia, biopsias, MRE.","guid":"9hVTAK9yI9H602PP5LgcMA","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"67","text":"• Colitis Ulcerosa\\N(CU):","guid":"pZuDlFtW60rxHbi1Onz77g","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"• Síntomas: Diarrea sanguinolenta, dolor abdominal, urgencia rectal.","guid":"EKbWymQ7x-zomHA4e2m7ZA","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"• Signos: Inflamación continua de la mucosa colónica.","guid":"ZAtZGc8CFblA_4HvGbrv2Q","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"72","text":"• Diagnóstico: Colonoscopia, biopsias.","guid":"2LamNGHUKSWoO9U7k1U4nQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"0","text":"Manejo de EII","guid":"666f1euOZ-H-735YbTAUjA","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"• Crohn:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"78","parent":"77","text":"• Manejo Médico:","guid":"JcqAPsqitQxryO1CHB_nkw","children":[{"id":"79","parent":"78","text":"• Enfermedad leve: 5-ASA, antibióticos.","guid":"5D-RwDzz2RXUOg_tUhWD-g","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"78","text":"• Moderada-grave: Corticoides, inmunomoduladores, biológicos (anti-TNF).","guid":"194q8DcQ3A_hvVjCb__GgA","children":[]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"77","text":"• Postquirúrgico:","guid":"NBR6HlGcO3vOMcrJvkw7NQ","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"• Monitoreo y prevención de recurrencias.","guid":"tMSPe6ieJDzugwDEQ5OjOw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"83","parent":"76","text":"• Colitis Ulcerosa:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"84","parent":"83","text":"• Manejo Médico:","guid":"SYb7vKoda1EAckdfBsDDEw","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"• Enfermedad leve-moderada: 5-ASA, corticoides.","guid":"UsufMd585fDRTj1840cfhQ","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"84","text":"• Grave: Inmunomoduladores, biológicos.","guid":"I7YOlpFfsqYT9srYE7EgRg","children":[]}]},{"id":"87","parent":"83","text":"• Paciente Hospitalizado:","guid":"PNggiUbURVcptMqOm_8vaQ","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"• Evaluación y manejo intensivo.","guid":"OtfMKBMQR6mgzi0r2IGJLw","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"0","text":"Sistema Inmunológico\\NMucoso","guid":"qrmbyzNWIfh3NudzMy2DOQ","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"Barreras Intestinales","guid":"WiKHWmbLCSzFXvd1YwFr7w","children":[{"id":"91","parent":"90","text":"• Epitelio intestinal: Intacto, mucosa secretada por células caliciformes.","guid":"5EnW1rPTF2E5016dLUFsYA","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"90","text":"• Peristalsis normal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"90","text":"• Factores protectores: Proteínas antimicrobianas, factores de crecimiento.","guid":"5Gos60ibYxyekBLuBBXkuQ","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"90","text":"• Células caliciformes: Transporte de antígenos al tejido subyacente (2).","guid":"nAZovAEMYV588AbimSDSXg","children":[]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"89","text":"Sistema Inmunológico\\NInnato","guid":"ksXjW_McMwSLzY1RVrpirg","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"• Células mieloides: Neutrófilos, monocitos, células dendríticas, macrófagos.","guid":"jkxERdKQ59HLPVjoZoPRvg","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"95","text":"• Células NK, células linfoides innatas","guid":"LHn8oZqK48ZZ9t8MYXyFhw","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"95","text":"• Receptores de reconocimiento de patrones: Expresados en células epiteliales, endoteliales y estromales → Respuesta inicial a microorganismos.","guid":"Ts_b9TJ7l4BoYOSY61QM7g","children":[]}]},{"id":"99","parent":"89","text":"Sistema Inmunológico\\NAdaptativo","guid":"3hOiRLMcQcyK-64NckdkbA","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"• Linfocitos B y T: Inmunidad específica.","guid":"NgSQaKWO0S45Pj3xSGJ8_Q","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"99","text":"• Células presentadoras de antígenos (APC): Células dendríticas, macrófagos.","guid":"hdsnWFBheNZhGOJn1aOCfQ","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"99","text":"• Inmunidad humoral: Linfocitos B → Secreción de IgA.","guid":"Oc044CZ_gF-Rpt24gmziig","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"99","text":"• Inmunidad celular: Linfocitos T → CD4+ y CD8+.","guid":"gP_4X_bFqeHUIb9nEnefuQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"89","text":"Subtipos de\\NLinfocitos T CD4+","guid":"dKQ_aOe0tqOy1fOgefbqUw","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"• Th1: Secreta IFN-γ, TNF-α, IL-2. Generación mediada por IL-12.","guid":"4O308VuUr3Bprm71qJXOFw","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"• Th2: Inducido por IL-4, secreta IL-4, IL-5, IL-13. Inhibido por IL-12.","guid":"3uSy9fr-bh0CqmXI94vs1w","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"104","text":"• Th17: Secreta IL-17, IL-21, IL-22, GM-CSF. Regulación de la inflamación mucosal.\\NImportancia del IL-23 en su mantenimiento (3-7).","guid":"9x_YH8FOMolX6PYp_B9aEA","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"104","text":"• Células T de memoria residentes en tejido (TRM): Retenidas localmente, responden rápidamente a antígenos.\\NExpresan CD69, CD154, producen IFN-γ, IL-17 (14).","guid":"3TyY4WfiI7o8FI0fANpxJw","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"104","text":"• Células T reguladoras (Treg): Subtipos incluyen Th3, Tr1, CD4+CD25+. Producen IL-10, TGF-β para regular Th1, Th2, Th17 (15).","guid":"RV5GoC6ks9Z4-hlMH3mGxw","children":[]}]},{"id":"110","parent":"89","text":"GALT (Tejido Linfoide\\NAsociado al Intestino)","guid":"D2v7BDREGStfQoG3InVDZw","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"• Distribución: Lámina propia, entre células epiteliales, estructuras linfoides.","guid":"S1-XmB2Q8hQi2rPeji8OEw","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"110","text":"• Células APC profesionales, leucocitos: Secreción de citocinas → Regulación de respuestas inmunes.","guid":"kFS717WaK3a9LYX1ut99Tg","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"110","text":"• Microcirculación, moléculas de tráfico, aferentes neuronales: Modifican composición y función de células inmunes y no inmunes.","guid":"UA1hB3NpHC9_oglNhhcT2Q","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"114","parent":"0","text":"Conceptos Clave en el Sistema\\NInmunológico Mucoso","guid":"xZ-M2SHgoJlwtp3sGhBE6A","children":[{"id":"115","parent":"114","text":"Equilibrio de la\\NRespuesta Inmune","guid":"27bkziFeqDwNbw6n360YDg","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"• Respuesta inmune adecuada: ↔ Evita inflamación intestinal.","guid":"bMBbb1Wlb6pmy_wnV6-aXg","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"• Excesiva/inadecuada: → Inflamación intestinal.","guid":"eBX8s2qUOxutj_BV4sSuOw","children":[]}]},{"id":"118","parent":"114","text":"Colaboración del Sistema\\NInmunológico Intestinal","guid":"cNYNyq2WOC3jCixnJ_IaBw","children":[{"id":"119","parent":"118","text":"• Defensa contra microbiota: Células cooperan para\\Neliminar microbios accediendo a tejidos intestinales.","guid":"n9WddLsO0CKVsOfF-WyP3w","children":[]}]},{"id":"120","parent":"114","text":"Mecanismos de Control de\\NRespuestas Excesivas","guid":"GGo6wmSsY0b5DnjFXL9VAA","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"• Macrófagos: Bajos niveles de citoquinas proinflamatorias, alta eficiencia en eliminar bacterias (16).\\NCaracterísticas antiinflamatorias (17, 18).","guid":"LfScQdCrnKKid_9w2PFpYg","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"120","text":"• Células dendríticas: Alta expresión de enzimas metabolizadoras de ácido retinoico → Trafico de linfocitos T y función de Treg (19-24).","guid":"yLvKdw2gbbclmP4fbyagHg","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"120","text":"• Treg: Eliminación de células T reactivas a bacterias luminales (25).","guid":"u8oDjS59h3KRqBFshKhEQQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"124","parent":"114","text":"Plasticidad de Subconjuntos de\\NCélulas Inmunológicas","guid":"tG4902JFevaYK2c6q5gCPg","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"• Transiciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"126","parent":"125","text":"• Th17 → Treg/Th2.","guid":"TfZNyya8dNe2hGcZBkcttg","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"125","text":"• Th1 → Th2.","guid":"Y8xlmz3dO5PoWg6bxt299g","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"125","text":"• Treg → IL-17+ / IFN-γ+ T cells (26-29).","guid":"WNi1QbjwsAiDIsQnvmVphg","children":[]}]},{"id":"129","parent":"124","text":"• Implicaciones\\Nterapéuticas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"• Terapia celular: Riesgo de transición a células patogénicas.","guid":"NBa9rSFiw1nsvJL-Cn8Ymg","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"• Inducción terapéutica: Transición de células patogénicas a reguladoras.","guid":"YfmF17oCIy9GhY0Yi4QvnQ","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"• Tecnologías de análisis unicelular: Mayor comprensión de transiciones celulares (30-35).","guid":"zzEJHVXmOpM7lTgKCkM22A","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"0","text":"Influencia del Ambiente Intestinal en\\NDiferenciación Inmunitaria","guid":"","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"• Factores:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"• Inflamación, mediadores secretados, microbiota, productos\\Nmetabólicos, dieta, exposiciones infecciosas previas (26, 27, 36-44).","guid":"-0GGoRk7kDlUTSyP7GXDxA","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"Sistema Nervioso\\NEntérico (SNE)","guid":"6YGKL5trsqwGgGwwXBENeQ","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"• Modulación del sistema\\Ninmune mucoso:","guid":"9SRwUnpYhiXLSP4p5SetRg","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"• Fibras simpáticas y parasimpáticas: Originadas del SNC.","guid":"1xTZItZVg5y_RTfErdHlmw","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"• Red intrínseca (neuronas y glía): Interacción con el tracto gastrointestinal,\\Nrecepción y envío de señales moduladoras (30, 45-47).","guid":"A7qo2dutPPgxPVW47pGivQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"140","parent":"133","text":"Disregulación\\NInmune y EII","guid":"NMdBEpF4aQAQuy30kNXP3w","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"Respuesta Inmune\\NDesregulada","guid":"sVBTLwbX_B-k8ahOtIXCCg","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"• EII: Respuesta desregulada del sistema inmune mucoso a la microbiota intestinal.","guid":"nYlyphsG1sHxWAPd5x8i-w","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"141","text":"• Desequilibrio: Excesiva reactividad inmune o respuestas insuficientes → Inflamación intestinal.","guid":"bVGtLLts8HOy91cE0eRPPQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"144","parent":"140","text":"Disregulación en la\\NBarrera Epitelial","guid":"_crmu9sEeUTSOj3iaJR9Kw","children":[{"id":"145","parent":"144","text":"• Alteraciones: Moco intestinal, permeabilidad aumentada, bacterias en el moco.","guid":"M-NPp4Fk0WFKkLzbdA27Ug","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"144","text":"• Modelos en\\Nratones:","guid":"FhK9LCkQRbd2TYOpGLAtBA","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"• Defectos en función de la barrera → Colitis espontánea (56-59).","guid":"wpfXqGWKstTZ1OJw2nvJkg","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"146","text":"• Células epiteliales:","guid":"88WQvHWPCJU38jYqWg9u7A","children":[{"id":"149","parent":"148","text":"• Expresan receptores inmunes, presentan antígenos.","guid":"Nt9tRFYs3VpgIyR-8et5pA","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"148","text":"• Presentación antigénica anormal → Interacción con linfocitos intraepiteliales (60-69).","guid":"cV07QF3ugnHu0lp79bO6Kw","children":[]}]},{"id":"151","parent":"146","text":"• Células de Paneth: Manejo de proteínas intracelulares no plegadas, estrés del RE, producción de proteínas antimicrobianas (70-74).","guid":"_4wFVTjwqL8GbkO6QgaP4Q","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"152","parent":"140","text":"Disregulación en\\NCélulas Inmunes","guid":"kwWaSqOZXdPE_SWcGxNwVw","children":[{"id":"153","parent":"152","text":"• Reclutamiento y\\Nactivación excesiva:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"• Células mieloides: Fenotipo inflamatorio, producción de citoquinas (36, 75-77).","guid":"1pjAuUYdt4BJjqvp9LlNaA","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"• Células NK: Subconjuntos alterados (78).","guid":"CuBeNVDPnmq6zlp6R6Tgjg","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"• Mononucleares: Marcadores de activación, citoquinas (34, 79).","guid":"6z_ld2hE8JxRHX31Mx52Fg","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"153","text":"• Linfocitos T: Proliferación y producción de citoquinas aumentada (80-86).","guid":"B3D64c4wR9DmFIT6Z3Pf7g","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"153","text":"• Células linfoides innatas: Desreguladas (87).","guid":"D6c-pKxNrCADeGjPY8YUWA","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"153","text":"• Linfocitos B y células plasmáticas: Aumento en número, autoanticuerpos (P-ANCA),\\Nanticuerpos contra componentes microbianos y citoquinas (53, 54, 88-94).","guid":"1-FT9qa2ZUotuFp13DzWww","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"153","text":"• Neutrófilos: Reclutados desde vasos sanguíneos → Rodamiento, adhesión firme, diapedesis (22, 96-99).","guid":"4wnsQlfo9_pIH_arTIzA5A","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"161","parent":"140","text":"Disregulación en\\NMediadores Secretados","guid":"VWLQyanWYnlV2hiTofp3VA","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"• Citoquinas\\Nproinflamatorias:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"163","parent":"162","text":"• Linfocitos T CD4+ (EC): IFN-γ, TNF-α (106-111) → Uso terapéutico de anti-TNF-α (112).","guid":"7FLNYw88pDbe4FM3Pp0ThA","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"162","text":"• Th2: IL-4, IL-5, IL-13 → Infiltración de eosinófilos, inflamación intestinal (113-116).","guid":"3uHE6tbHssO0-gBg2_oPqA","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"162","text":"• Th17: IL-17, IL-23 (4, 117-131) → Células más patogénicas condicionadas por IL-23 (132-134).","guid":"9H0U90P1xjM1axxYe1prKg","children":[]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"161","text":"• Células\\Nreguladoras:","guid":"6mxrYVwYC6JfreUy_zv7_g","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"• Tregs (CD4+CD25+FOXP3+): Secreción de IL-10, TGF-β (15, 135).","guid":"K1prBXYLCIqUcIALOvv3Xw","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"166","text":"• T CD8+: Secreción de IL-10, TGF-β.","guid":"NaQxlxvPTv0TXUuveURKYg","children":[]}]},{"id":"169","parent":"161","text":"• Eje TL1A/DR3\\N(EC):","guid":"UWI-Okjqc1ZFJft244UCHQ","children":[{"id":"170","parent":"169","text":"• TL1A: Citoquina tipo TNF, interactúa con receptor DR3.","guid":"VQRsKVvd_ooFUj8GSG3dsQ","children":[]},{"id":"171","parent":"169","text":"• Inducción de citoquinas: Th1, Th2, Th17, NK, mieloides, linfoides innatas (138-145).","guid":"9EjIll7f5KzxB-LUt1SyTw","children":[]}]},{"id":"172","parent":"161","text":"Otros Productos\\NBiológicos en EII","guid":"SE0M0ngrLBYiNZOpHCeq4w","children":[{"id":"173","parent":"172","text":"• Exceso: Ácido araquidónico, productos\\Nreactivos de oxígeno y nitrógeno.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"0","text":"Rol de los Microbios\\Nen la EII","guid":"XC4E3xWR-ub4jEJkAle48A","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"Interacciones\\NHuésped-Microbiota","guid":"xP4lGCsBQO5nwzOIL9VTqQ","children":[{"id":"176","parent":"175","text":"• Microbiota intestinal: Alta concentración en íleon distal y colon.","guid":"b3nAKUcx1eXpc9RCS08ZzA","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"175","text":"• Interacciones\\Nbidireccionales:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"178","parent":"177","text":"• Beneficiosas: Nutrición, metabolismo energético, “condicionamiento” inmune.","guid":"Dk2zWDlmZihD5ehgsmuzHg","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"177","text":"• Adversas: Contribuyen a inflamación intestinal en contexto de defectos inmunes genéticos.","guid":"BQyVYG40O_R_dJktxAGyDg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"174","text":"Adquisición y Modulación\\Nde la Microbiota","guid":"EJTgCM48sikE2VapZ9wmyA","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"• Nacimiento: Adquisición de la microbiota.","guid":"cyEA926zgWBIYwU4CeLB6g","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"180","text":"• Adultos: Población microbiana estable pero influenciada por factores ambientales y enfermedades (152).","guid":"wlroMJ_ALgUkK2-TZuRXDg","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"180","text":"• Función de la microbiota: Moduladores del metabolismo energético (153, 154).","guid":"jOYvyBGxZbe5Y04rtSfwuA","children":[]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"174","text":"Influencia en el\\NSistema Inmune","guid":"v5csXF9XCmKGHDkMFeEw8A","children":[{"id":"185","parent":"184","text":"• Microbiota:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"186","parent":"185","text":"• Generación y función óptima de proteínas antimicrobianas, células epiteliales, células linfoides innatas,\\Ncélulas NK, linfocitos T productores de IL-17, Tregs e IgA (42, 155-171).","guid":"TdJ2hFMkSWQhrVDxSS2VDw","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"185","text":"• Sistema inmune y condiciones del huésped (obesidad): Modulan comunidades microbianas (57, 172-177).","guid":"ymw_HDZ3Bfto3ZAaFgegOA","children":[]}]},{"id":"188","parent":"184","text":"• Factores ambientales: Dieta, exposición a helmintos, uso de antibióticos (177-185).","guid":"UeFSpki9G0qb-1LjoG5xKA","children":[]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"174","text":"Alteraciones\\NMicrobianas en EII","guid":"FmUeuZ_vdQuaXjRO3GgQTg","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"• Pacientes con EII:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"• Cambios en diversidad y densidad bacteriana.","guid":"cEdgEhPPk8eOFCkvwRIKyw","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"190","text":"• Bacterias asociadas a la mucosa.","guid":"ZHrAsSsI87XuoFlZV2seZg","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"190","text":"• Funciones bacterianas (estrés oxidativo, regulación nutricional) (186-191).","guid":"nCEAfxMNIkWx_5ocSq7yMQ","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"190","text":"• Niños con EII: Alteraciones microbianas al diagnóstico inicial (190).","guid":"3O8sOFJF7auv5a-EUoRzmg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"195","parent":"174","text":"Respuesta Inmune a\\NComponentes Microbianos","guid":"wE3dzRdRXs4fclqHuj5qIg","children":[{"id":"196","parent":"195","text":"• Anticuerpos a\\Ncomponentes microbianos:","guid":"1U6HjO08d4sRy1GPB-a0XA","children":[{"id":"197","parent":"196","text":"• DNA segmento (I2) en EC (194).","guid":"JN-a8u7oOnL1o2as6v69lA","children":[]},{"id":"198","parent":"196","text":"• Flagelina bacteriana en EC complicada (195, 196).","guid":"GEyXLM748bt_J6KMvSwpLA","children":[]},{"id":"199","parent":"196","text":"• Correlación con EII agresiva (197, 198).","guid":"LVbtw1OlSOL8lDudnrlXCA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"200","parent":"174","text":"Cirugía de\\NAnastomosis Ileoanal","guid":"kTS0ILDrY1gNQboOgBKnHA","children":[{"id":"201","parent":"200","text":"• Correlaciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"202","parent":"201","text":"• Microbiota, expresión génica mucosa, resultados clínicos\\N(pouchitis) (199-201).","guid":"2bV9rdVj7uZeHbHImea7hg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"203","parent":"174","text":"Modelos\\NMurinos de EII","guid":"P1L-t2RDWubGeLJlzzQdhw","children":[{"id":"204","parent":"203","text":"• Inflamación intestinal en presencia de microflora normal: No en condiciones libres de gérmenes (197, 202, 203).","guid":"vp-oW1cUnWuuqrNnSZU17g","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"203","text":"• Transferencia bacteriana: Promueve inflamación intestinal (173, 174).","guid":"OSXY6goRdHuS4i890ChD2g","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"203","text":"• Bacterias combinadas con defectos genéticos: Resultan en inflamación (204).","guid":"X56Y3694eyxvZC2z5e_5eQ","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"203","text":"• Bacterias cubiertas por IgA: Promueven inflamación (205).","guid":"vsjZD7uEKBkVGlbl8hxo_g","childre