"text":"Modulación de\\NExpresión","guid":"6nb5Mj44S3UYvdcfxBl9qQ","children":[{"id":"222","parent":"221","text":"• Regiones intrónicas: Variantes que no alteran aminoácidos, modulan expresión de proteínas.","guid":"ML50PNTbwgs38SXGc5bsUA","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"221","text":"• Disrupción leve: Cada locus confiere aumento leve en el riesgo de enfermedad.","guid":"oeH33tx6HgzApeUpkbOI1A","children":[]}]},{"id":"224","parent":"217","text":"Enfermedad de Inicio Temprano","guid":"1t_BkDniFELd8IVbXMT_3Q","children":[{"id":"225","parent":"224","text":"• Variantes genéticas: Mayor disrupción → EII de inicio muy temprano (223).","guid":"TnSDQNNCiuO1OFv5dA9Jrg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"226","parent":"0","text":"Asociación con Otras\\NEnfermedades","guid":"57_kP4wQFRwpqomAGeUnYA","children":[{"id":"227","parent":"226","text":"• Enfermedades mediadas por el sistema inmune.","guid":"_JrCbNkmAVk2BGV-6FHA3A","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"226","text":"• Inmunodeficiencias y susceptibilidad a enfermedades micobacterianas (146).","guid":"vV_19THKoLbLpK790OWgpw","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"226","text":"Vías Inmunes\\NInnatas","guid":"dqxPXQb1mlCWRwTAkeLJrw","children":[{"id":"230","parent":"229","text":"• NOD2:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"231","parent":"230","text":"• Primera identificada para EC (224, 225).","guid":"xsbTHieVwY4cD8LCHfHuCQ","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"230","text":"• Respuesta a peptidoglicano bacteriano → Activación de vías de señalización,\\Nproducción de citoquinas, eliminación de bacterias (226).","guid":"1nYbKyJ_0GvyCo34ZFTldw","children":[]},{"id":"233","parent":"230","text":"• Variantes: Pérdida de función, aumento de susceptibilidad a patógenos entéricos (227, 228).","guid":"n38Cqe2MB7WZBXkzApu16Q","children":[]},{"id":"234","parent":"230","text":"• Expresión en varios tipos celulares: Células epiteliales, macrófagos, dendríticas, endoteliales, estromales (226).","guid":"43TDkYl2F9KuhGn7Xl2pvQ","children":[]},{"id":"235","parent":"230","text":"• Riesgo:","guid":"BydveRUCZ2FikcUSxD1--A","children":[{"id":"236","parent":"235","text":"• 1 alelo mutante → Aumento 1.5-3.7 veces.","guid":"U-BQD2y3KM1gu0QFvko2hg","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"235","text":"• 2 alelos mutantes → Aumento 17-40 veces (232-235).","guid":"-NLSZvtllTx__qeSOCpPMw","children":[]},{"id":"238","parent":"235","text":"• Asociación con edad temprana, EC ileal, fibroestenótica, peores resultados post-cirugía (232, 233, 238-242).","guid":"0_pH2qBuZdXbn4lF7LOIJg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"239","parent":"229","text":"• Otros genes de\\Nvías innatas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"240","parent":"239","text":"• Variantes que aumentan respuestas innatas (IRF5, TNFSF15, TPL2, JAK2, STAT1/STAT4, STAT3/STAT5)\\N→ Mayor producción de citoquinas (144, 244-252).","guid":"5XmCyvW2ELP1LpLYlCIKNg","children":[]},{"id":"241","parent":"239","text":"• Variantes que disminuyen respuestas innatas (ICOSLG, INAVA, LACC1, RNF186)\\N→ Menor eliminación bacteriana (253-260).","guid":"08lzVLyj1bQgHabLrV9sJA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"242","parent":"226","text":"Vías de Eliminación\\NMicrobiana","guid":"GD1MoTvDQisO28_Plmox3A","children":[{"id":"243","parent":"242","text":"• ATG16L1, IRGM:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"244","parent":"243","text":"• Autofagia: Eliminación de patógenos intracelulares (261-267).","guid":"F5le_MmOqUIth2UDloVw5Q","children":[]},{"id":"245","parent":"243","text":"• Mutaciones: Cambios en células de Paneth y caliciformes, menor\\Neliminación bacteriana, mayor secreción de citoquinas (73, 74, 268, 269).","guid":"1q9s8ZW_5UiyJCRcSKgIvA","children":[]}]},{"id":"246","parent":"242","text":"• Genes de NADPH oxidasa: Regulación de especies reactivas de oxígeno, clearance microbiano (271, 272).","guid":"64HYLU8-y0SZaptRJ0VxYw","children":[]}]},{"id":"247","parent":"226","text":"Vías de\\NCitoquinas","guid":"iT9E5K-nM4qEzJ5OA33NYQ","children":[{"id":"248","parent":"247","text":"• Th17/IL-23:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"249","parent":"248","text":"• Variantes de IL-23R asociadas a EC y CU (5-7, 146, 148).","guid":"cGy6lR9OTr9xSbbS4ZuhLw","children":[]},{"id":"250","parent":"248","text":"• STAT3, JAK2, TYK2, IL12B, RORC: Genes en la misma vía (146-148, 263).","guid":"thV3SphiCKtmAibvx6xX7w","children":[]}]},{"id":"251","parent":"247","text":"• IL-10:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"252","parent":"251","text":"• Variantes comunes y raras asociadas a EII (146, 284-286).","guid":"gZ9k4NSobo3F09dySANEmQ","children":[]},{"id":"253","parent":"251","text":"• Deficiencia IL-10: Colitis espontánea en modelos murinos (106, 111).","guid":"Hxs6d7LHrqa-bvE05fYq6Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"254","parent":"247","text":"• TNFSF15:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"255","parent":"254","text":"• Variantes aumentan expresión de TNFSF15 (144, 250).","guid":"csQPaqq3nB6sD265DL-wfA","children":[]},{"id":"256","parent":"254","text":"• Asociación en poblaciones de ascendencia europea y asiática (149-151).","guid":"yS0jxVC3AUoX4U3bu7dnEg","children":[]}]},{"id":"257","parent":"247","text":"• IL18R/IL1R:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"258","parent":"257","text":"• Variantes disminuyen expresión de IL18RAP, IL18R1, IL1R1 en células innatas\\N→ Menor respuesta a IL-18 y IL-1β (290).","guid":"XOeyoTCsrX4Ind12STmBOg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"259","parent":"0","text":"Vías Adaptativas\\Ny Epiteliales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"260","parent":"259","text":"• Vías adaptativas: IRF5, IL23R, PTPN2, PTPN22.","guid":"nuUY7mRIq8hrAz7tsXjGgw","children":[{"id":"261","parent":"260","text":"• PTPN2: Aumenta Th1 y Th17, disminuye marcadores Treg (292).","guid":"wghsMlGf4KTB4lepIs1Z_g","children":[]}]},{"id":"262","parent":"259","text":"• Vías epiteliales:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"263","parent":"262","text":"• XBP1, ORMDL3: Regulación de la respuesta a proteínas no plegadas (70).","guid":"W3oodIInh2d2v1LyL4lbiQ","children":[]},{"id":"264","parent":"262","text":"• ATG16L1, PTPN2, INAVA, RNF186, A20: Regulación en combinac